cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper discusses a new framework for analyzing citation content in the context of research behavior, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on analyzing text and language suggests that cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the use of natural language processing techniques for syntactic and semantic analysis suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another likely sub-category. The sociocultural context of research behavior could also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
